British Petroleum Co Plc &lt;BP.L> said itis proposing a capitalisation share issue of two new ordinaryshares for each ordinary share held at the close of business onApril 15.    The move is subject to the approval of shareholders at anextraordinary general meeting to be held on April 30, it saidin a statement.    The new shares will not participate in the proposed finaldividend for 1986, expected to be paid on May 7. REUTER&#3;